Introduction¶

  • This projects aims to apply CoSTA pipeline on Visium datasets. Also modify CoSTA architecture to include transformer layers.
  • Here we've used the 10X Genomics Visium 4 human prostate sample downloaded from here 10X Genomics Datasets.
  • Samples were initially analyzed using Seurat V4 spaital data analysis pipeline Here. creating_gene_exp_images.Rmd notebook was used to generate the spatial gene expression images from the samples. Briefly, each dataset was imported using Load10X_Spatial function, then normalized using SCTransform() function, then filtered for top highly variable 3000 genes, then gene expression images (200*200) were generated using SpatialFeaturePlot()`.
  • Images were processed to (85*85) grayscale images to make computational faster, and all images were concatenated in (3000,1,85,85) array.

Analyzing Acinar Cell Carcinoma Sample¶

Loading the processing images array¶

Here We're loading the spatial gene expression arrays generated in the converting_images_to_np_array notebook. We'll be using the 85*85 images array. Then we're plotting the frequency of the mean pixel intensity of the genes images to filter out images with mostly background. We're setting the cut-off to 20. Then we're normalizng the pixels intensity values across all images as described in the paper.

In [90]:
h,w = 85,85
dataset = np.load("../results/HVGeneExpArrays_85/acinar_cell_carcinoma.npy")
genes = listdir("../results/HVGeneExpImgs/acinar_cell_carcinoma/")
genes = [re.sub('.jpeg$', '', gene) for gene in genes]
dataset = dataset.reshape(dataset.shape[0],1,h,w)
In [91]:
n, bins, patches = plt.hist(x= np.mean(dataset.reshape(dataset.shape[0],85*85), axis =1), bins='auto', color='#0504aa',
                            alpha=0.7, rwidth=0.85)
plt.grid(axis='y', alpha=0.75)
plt.xlabel('Value')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')
plt.title('Mean Pixel Value Freq')
maxfreq = n.max()
plt.ylim(ymax=np.ceil(maxfreq / 10) * 10 if maxfreq % 10 else maxfreq + 10)

Loading model¶

Here we're using the same model described in the paper. We only changed the stride of the first layer to 1 as this showed superior performance

In [219]:
net = model.ConvNet85()
net.apply(utils.weights_init)
device = torch.device("cuda" if torch.cuda.is_available() else "cpu")
net
Out[219]:
ConvNet85(
  (layer1): Sequential(
    (0): Conv2d(1, 128, kernel_size=(11, 11), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    (1): BatchNorm2d(128, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
    (2): ReLU()
    (3): MaxPool2d(kernel_size=2, stride=2, padding=0, dilation=1, ceil_mode=False)
  )
  (layer2): Sequential(
    (0): Conv2d(128, 128, kernel_size=(7, 7), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    (1): BatchNorm2d(128, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
    (2): ReLU()
    (3): MaxPool2d(kernel_size=2, stride=2, padding=0, dilation=1, ceil_mode=False)
  )
  (layer3): Sequential(
    (0): Conv2d(128, 128, kernel_size=(5, 5), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
    (1): BatchNorm2d(128, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
    (2): ReLU()
    (3): MaxPool2d(kernel_size=2, stride=2, padding=0, dilation=1, ceil_mode=False)
  )
  (dropout): Dropout(p=0.5, inplace=False)
  (fc2): Linear(in_features=6272, out_features=10, bias=True)
)

##visualization without training
import umap.umap_ as umap
X_all_tensor = torch.tensor(dataset).float()
y_pred = net.forward_feature(X_all_tensor)
y_pred = torch.Tensor.cpu(y_pred).detach().numpy()
au_tar, y_label, embedding = utils.evaluation(y_pred,n_neighbors=5,min_dist=0.0,
                                        num_cluster=10,cluster_method='GMM') 
original = y_label.copy()
embedding = umap.UMAP(n_neighbors=5, min_dist=0.0, n_components=2,
                      metric='correlation').fit_transform(y_pred)

In [38]:
# Interacitve UMAP
import umap.umap_ as umap
embedding = umap.UMAP(n_neighbors=15, min_dist=0.3, n_components=2,
                      metric='correlation').fit(y_pred)
import umap.plot
hover_data = pd.DataFrame(
{'cluster':np.argmax(au_tar, axis = 1),
 'Gene': genes,
 'Index': range(dataset.shape[0])})
p = umap.plot.interactive(embedding, labels= np.argmax(au_tar, axis = 1), hover_data=hover_data, point_size=5,color_key_cmap='Paired', background='black')
umap.plot.show(p)
